# Estate Rooms™ Framework (T-017)

**Full document:** `docs/ESTATE_ROOMS_FRAMEWORK.md`

**Conversation integration:** [Spec 108 — Environment Integration](../docs/SPARK_ENVIRONMENT_INTEGRATION_FRAMEWORK.md)

**Workspace surface:** [Spec 109 — Frosted Conversation Workspace](../docs/SPARK_FROSTED_CONVERSATION_WORKSPACE_FRAMEWORK.md)

Rooms are **not** backgrounds or themes. The Estate™ is Spark's interface. Every room must improve thinking **before** work begins.

## The Estate Principle™ (all three required)

1. Why does this room exist?
2. How does this environment improve the member's thinking?
3. What transformation happens here?

Unanswerable → room should not exist.

**Type:** `ESTATE_PRINCIPLE_QUESTIONS` · `SparkEstateRoomSpec` in `lib/sparkEstateRooms/types.ts`

## One room · one purpose · one emotion

Clear My Mind (relief) · Focus (concentration) · Grow (possibility) · Create (creative confidence) · Gallery (pride) · Observatory (wonder) · Guild Hall (mastery) · Community (belonging)

Never multi-purpose rooms. Never mix competing emotions.

## Architectural identity

Stone · wood · glass · books · plants · fire · water · natural light · timeless craft.

**Never:** sci-fi · corporate office · cartoon.

Living spaces feel **inhabited** — open books, coffee, notes, soft lantern light ([Estate Light Flicker](./estate-light-flicker.mdc)).

## Environment responds

**Time:** morning golden · afternoon productive · evening warm lamps · night quiet.

**Season:** spring/summer/autumn/winter — decor evolves, identity stays.

**Personalization:** notebook, assets on desk, gallery frames, open Spark Cards — room becomes *theirs*.

## Orientation (no instructions required)

Why am I here? · What happens here? · What should I do first?

Reduce EF load — limit choices, hide complexity, support return and continuation.

## Required spec fields (new rooms)

Primary purpose · emotional goal · capability · environmental psychology · time/season · personalization · connected rooms · EF strategy · ambient sound · Business Asset link when relevant.

## V1 runtime

`lib/companionHomestead/homesteadRoomRegistry.ts` — backgrounds, signature motion, section mapping.

Also: Spec 103 Universal Experience · T-014 Connection · T-010 Journey · [07 Estate Navigation](../spark-intelligence-foundation/07-estate-navigation.md).

## Competitive advantage

Members say *"I spent the morning in my Grow Room"* — not *"I used an app."*
